Let $\mathbf{a} = \begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ 2 \\ 3 \end{pmatrix},$ $\mathbf{b} = \begin{pmatrix} 6 \\ 7 \\ 7 \end{pmatrix},$ and $\mathbf{d} = \begin{pmatrix} 3 \\ 2 \\ -2 \end{pmatrix}.$  Then the vector projection of $\mathbf{a} - \mathbf{b}$ onto $\mathbf{d}$ is
\[\operatorname{proj}_{\mathbf{d}} (\mathbf{a} - \mathbf{b}) = \frac{(\mathbf{a} - \mathbf{b}) \cdot \mathbf{d}}{\mathbf{d} \cdot \mathbf{d}} \mathbf{d} = \frac{\begin{pmatrix} -5 \\ -5 \\ -4 \end{pmatrix} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} 3 \\ 2 \\ -2 \end{pmatrix}}{\begin{pmatrix} 3 \\ 2 \\ -2 \end{pmatrix} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} 3 \\ 2 \\ -2 \end{pmatrix}} \begin{pmatrix} 3 \\ 2 \\ -2 \end{pmatrix} = -\frac{13}{17} \begin{pmatrix} 3 \\ 2 \\ -2 \end{pmatrix}.\][asy]
import three;

size(180);
currentprojection = perspective(6,3,2);

triple I = (1,0,0), J = (0,1,0), K = (0,0,1);
triple A = (1,2,3), B = (6,7,7), D = (3,2,-2), P = (6,7,7) - 13/17*(3,2,-2);

draw(surface((2*I + 2*J)--(2*I - 2*J)--(-2*I - 2*J)--(-2*I + 2*J)--cycle),paleyellow,nolight);
draw((2*I + 2*J)--(2*I - 2*J)--(-2*I - 2*J)--(-2*I + 2*J)--cycle);
draw((0,-1,0)--(0,10,0),dashed);
draw((-1,0,0)--(8,0,0));
draw((0,0,-1)--(0,0,8));
draw(B--B + D,Arrow3(6));
draw(B--A,Arrow3(6));
draw(B--P,Arrow3(6));

label("$\mathbf{b}$", B, N);
label("$\mathbf{a}$", A, N);
label("$\mathbf{d}$", (B + D)/2, N);
label("$\mathbf{a} - \mathbf{b}$", (A + B)/2, S);
label("$\operatorname{proj}_{\mathbf{d}} (\mathbf{a} - \mathbf{b})$", (B + P)/2, W);
[/asy]

The distance from $(1,2,3)$ to the line is then the length of the vector $\mathbf{a} - \mathbf{b} - \operatorname{proj}_{\mathbf{d}} (\mathbf{a} - \mathbf{b}),$ which is
\[\left\| \begin{pmatrix} -5 \\ -5 \\ -4 \end{pmatrix} + \frac{13}{17} \begin{pmatrix} 3 \\ 2 \\ -2 \end{pmatrix} \right\| = \left\| \begin{pmatrix} -26/17 \\ -69/17 \\ -58/17 \end{pmatrix} \right\| = \boxed{\frac{\sqrt{9461}}{17}}.\]

